==English==

===Etymology===
From {{OF.}} ''coillir'' "collect, gather, select," from {{L.}} ''colligere'' "gather together."

===Pronunciation===

*[[Pronunciation guide|IPA]]:/kʌl/
*:Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-ʌl|-ʌl]]

===Verb===
{{en-verb}}

# To [[pick]] something.
# To [[take]] something (from somewhere).
# To [[select]] animals from a group and kill them in order to reduce the numbers of the group in a controlled way
# (''non-standard, euphemism'') To [[kill]] animals.

====Quotations====
*'''1984''', cover star: JOE DALLESANDRO '''culled''' from Andy Warhol's FLESH &mdash; anonymous, ''Sleeve notes from [[w:The Smiths|The Smiths]]' album The Smiths''

